# Outbound sender rewriting for the Mailgun relay path (smtp_generic_maps),
# applied by smtp(8) at delivery -- after masquerade has collapsed system mail
# to root@{{ domain }}. The lowest-precedence @domain rule rewrites any sender
# left on {{ domain }} to the same localpart at {{ email_domain }} (the
# Mailgun-authorized domain the service roles send from), so cron/smartd/`mail`
# all share one sending identity. `@otherdomain` keeps the localpart per
# generic(5) RESULT ADDRESS REWRITING; recipients are external so never match.
@{{ domain }}    @{{ email_domain }}
